        <body>
            <div type="original">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP013_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Protokol</hi>
                </p>
                <p>který jest opsán dle původního, pí. <persName ref="#ehri_et_morgensternova_ruth" type="ehri">Ruth Morgensternovou</persName>
                    podepsaného protokolu, bytem <placeName ref="#brno" type="ehri">Brno</placeName>, <placeName ref="#brno" type="ehri">Na
                        ponávce</placeName> 10</p>
                <p>bývalým <term ref="#t483" type="subject">vězněm</term>
                    <term ref="#t496" type="subject">koncentr. tábora</term>
                    <placeName ref="#l42" type="camp">Bergen-Belsen</placeName> a <term ref="#t508" type="subject">prac. táb.</term> v <placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Estonsku</placeName></p>
                <p><term ref="#t267" type="subject">Transport Be Terezín</term> - <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri"
                        >Estonsko</placeName>.</p>
                <p><date when="1942-09-01">I. IX. 1942</date>
                    <term ref="#t267" type="subject">odjezd z Terezína</term>, směr <placeName ref="#l1032" type="ehri">Riga</placeName>. Cesta byla
                    dobrá, doprovod slušný. V <placeName ref="#l1032" type="ehri">Rize</placeName> stojíme den, pak odjíždíme dále, do <placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Estonska</placeName>. Po pětidenní cestě <term ref="#t522" type="subject">vlak</term>
                    staví 25 km od <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinu</placeName> v <placeName ref="#raasiku" type="ehri"
                        >Raasiku</placeName>. Tam nás čeká <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term> a <orgName ref="#g356" type="ehri">SD</orgName>
                    s modrými, krásnými autobusy. Stojíme před <term ref="#t522" type="subject">vlakem</term> a jeden <term ref="#t1216"
                        type="subject">SSman</term> vybírá mladé lidi, kteří prý půjdou pěšky. Ostatní jsou vyzváni odložit zavazadla a vstoupit do
                    autobusu. Od té doby není od nich zpráv. My mladí (75 <term ref="#t825" type="subject">žen</term> a asi 150 <term ref="#t826"
                        type="subject">mužů</term>) odjíždíme na nákladních autech se zavazadly od celého <term ref="#t521" type="subject"
                        >transportu</term> do nedalekého <term ref="#t508" type="subject">tábora</term>
                    <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">JAGALLA</placeName>. Je to <term ref="#t508" type="subject">tábor</term> uprostřed lesa, se
                    starými, rozbitými <term ref="#t837" type="subject">barákami</term>, ohraničený ostnatým drátem. <term ref="#t482" type="subject"
                        >Lagerführer</term>
                    <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">estonský</placeName>
                    <orgName ref="#g356" type="ehri">SDman</orgName>, jeho adjutant baltický <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject"
                        >Němec</term>. Hlídka je <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">estonská</placeName>. Prvý večer jsou nám odebrány
                    cenné věci a přebytečné <term ref="#t836" type="subject">šaty</term>. (tělesná prohlídka). <term ref="#t836" type="subject"
                        >Šaty</term> nám byly příští den navráceny. Po třech dnech nás odvádí do velkých <term ref="#t837" type="subject"
                        >baráků</term>, kde třídíme a vybalujeme věci z našeho <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transportu</term>. <term ref="#t826"
                        type="subject">Muže</term>, které vidíme jen zdaleka, posílají na lesní <term ref="#t508" type="subject">práce</term>, odkud
                    se k nám vracejí jen <term ref="#t292" type="subject">nemocní</term>, kteří jsou zas posíláni dál, prý do <placeName ref="#tartu"
                        type="ehri">Dorpatu</placeName>, kde je <term ref="#t282" type="subject">lazaret</term>. Tam prý je i zbytek <term ref="#t521"
                        type="subject">transportu</term>, ale nikdy jsme od žádného <placeName ref="#tartu" type="ehri">dorpatského</placeName>
                    obyvatele neslyšeli, že jsou tam Židé. Zacházení se <term ref="#t825" type="subject">ženami</term> dobré, <term ref="#t826"
                        type="subject">mužům</term> se daří hůř, zvlášť venku na <term ref="#t556" type="subject">práci</term>, kde je <placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Estonci</placeName> oberou a nedávají jim <term ref="#t832" type="subject">jíst</term>.
                        <term ref="#t832" type="subject">Jídlo</term> je poměrně dobré, možnost spojení se světem není. V <date when="1942-10"
                        >říjnu</date> přichází další <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term> z <placeName
                        ref="#federal-republic-of-germany " type="ehri">Německa</placeName> (<placeName ref="#frankfurt-am-main" type="ehri"
                        >Frankfurt</placeName> a <placeName ref="#berlin" type="ehri">Berlin</placeName>). Opět zavazadla a část lidí do <placeName
                        ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Jagälly</placeName>. V <date when="1942-12">prosinci</date> odjíždí velký <term ref="#t521"
                        type="subject">transport</term>
                    <term ref="#t825" type="subject">žen</term> do <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Revalu (Tallin)</placeName> a prý do
                        <placeName ref="#tartu" type="ehri">Dorpatu</placeName> (tam jen <term ref="#t274" type="subject">starší</term> a <term
                        ref="#t292" type="subject">nemocní</term>). Zbytek <term ref="#t825" type="subject">žen</term> se <term ref="#t837"
                        type="subject">stěhuje</term> do velmi pěkných <term ref="#t837" type="subject">baraků</term> (je jich 45 téměř samé <term
                        ref="#t279" type="subject">Češky</term>). Po skončení <term ref="#t556" type="subject">práce</term> ve <term ref="#t48312"
                        type="subject">Schleusce</term> chodí <term ref="#t825" type="subject">ženy</term> do lesa <term ref="#t556" type="subject"
                        >kácet</term> stromy a <term ref="#t556" type="subject">bourat</term> staré baráky. <term ref="#t556" type="subject"
                        >Práce</term> jest velmi těžká. V <date when="1943-08">srpnu 1943</date> odjíždí zbytek <term ref="#t825" type="subject"
                        >žen</term> do <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinu</placeName>, <term ref="#t508" type="subject">tábor</term> se
                    likviduje. Před odjezdem je nám většina věcí odebrána. V <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinu</placeName>
                    <term ref="#t837" type="subject">bydlíme</term> v centrálním <term ref="#t669" type="subject">vězení</term>, kde se setkáváme
                    s prvním <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transportem</term>, <term ref="#t556" type="subject">pracujeme</term> společně na
                    odklízecích <term ref="#t556" type="subject">pracích</term> v přístavu pod dohledem <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri"
                        >O.T.</orgName> Tam též vídáme <term ref="#t826" type="subject">muže</term> z našeho <term ref="#t521" type="subject"
                        >transportu</term>, kteří po skončených <term ref="#t556" type="subject">pracích</term> přicházejí rovněž do <term ref="#t669"
                        type="subject">vězení</term>. <term ref="#t832" type="subject">Strava</term> ve <term ref="#t669" type="subject">vězení</term>
                    je hrozná, ale máme možnost si občas něco zaopatřit.</p>
                <p>V <date when="1943-12">prosinci 1943</date> odjíždějí všechny <term ref="#t825" type="subject">ženy</term> z <placeName
                        ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinu</placeName> do <placeName ref="#ereda" type="ehri">EREDY</placeName> t. j. asi 30 km od
                        <placeName ref="#narva" type="ehri">Narvy</placeName>. <term ref="#t826" type="subject">Muži</term> zůstanou v <placeName
                        ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinu</placeName>, odkud máme v <date when="1944-03">březnu 1944</date> od nich poslední zprávu.
                        <placeName ref="#ereda" type="ehri">Ereda</placeName> je malý <term ref="#t508" type="subject">tábor</term>, kde už je asi 1
                    000 Židů z <placeName ref="#republic-of-lithuania" type="ehri">Litvy</placeName> (<placeName ref="#vilnius" type="ehri"
                        >Vilno</placeName> a <placeName ref="#kaunas" type="ehri">Kovno</placeName>) a <placeName ref="#republic-of-latvia"
                        type="ehri">Lotyšska</placeName>. Jsou <term ref="#t213" type="subject">zavšivení</term> a bez věcí. V okolí je ještě několik
                    podobných <term ref="#t508" type="subject">táborů</term>. I několik <term ref="#t279" type="subject">Čechů</term> je tam, kteří
                    přicházejí z <placeName ref="#l1032" type="ehri">Rigy</placeName>. Vedení tu již má <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term>,
                    dozor <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Est.</placeName> a <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri">O.T.</orgName>
                    <term ref="#t832" type="subject">Strava</term> špatná, ale možnost si něco zaopatřit, ovšem pro odvážné. <term ref="#t556"
                        type="subject">Pracuje</term> se v lese a na výstavbě nového <term ref="#t508" type="subject">tábora</term>, který je několik
                    km vzdálen. Je tu <term ref="#t493" type="subject">tyfus</term>, <term ref="#t292" type="subject">nemocní</term>, <term
                        ref="#t274" type="subject">staří</term> a <term ref="#t824" type="subject">děti</term> jsou stále posíláni pryč (pravděpodobně
                    do <placeName ref="#l0" type="camp">Osvěnčíma</placeName>). Když se <orgName ref="#g004583" type="ehri">Rusové</orgName> blíží, (v
                        <date when="1944-07">červenci 1944</date>), odjíždíme do <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinu</placeName>, kde má být
                    pro nás loď. Ta tu není, a proto vystupujeme v předměstí <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinu</placeName> na velké louce,
                    kde zůstáváme bez <term ref="#t837" type="subject">přístřeší</term> tři neděle. Chodíme <term ref="#t556" type="subject">kopat
                        zákopy</term>. V <term ref="#t508" type="subject">táboře</term> je velký <term ref="#t569" type="subject">hlad</term>. V <date
                        when="1944-08">srpnu</date> odjíždíme konečně lodí do <placeName ref="#federal-republic-of-germany " type="ehri"
                        >Německa</placeName>. Jedeme pět dní bez <term ref="#t832" type="subject">jídla</term>. Přijíždíme do <placeName ref="#gdansk"
                        type="ehri">Danzigu</placeName> a odtud po <placeName ref="#ehri_et_vistula" type="ehri">Visle</placeName> do <placeName
                        ref="#l857" type="ehri">Stutthofu</placeName>. Tam procházíme koupelí, jsou nám odebrány věci a dány nové <term ref="#t836"
                        type="subject">šaty</term>. Ostříhány jsme už byly před odjezdem z <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri"
                        >Estonska</placeName>. <term ref="#t556" type="subject">Práce</term> schopné <term ref="#t825" type="subject">ženy</term>
                    odjíždějí po třech nedělích do <placeName ref="#hamburg" type="ehri">Hamburku</placeName> na <term ref="#t556" type="subject"
                        >práci</term> do muniční <term ref="#t929" type="subject">továrny</term>. Odtud jsme v <date when="1945-04">dubnu 1945</date>
                    evakuovány do <placeName ref="#l42" type="camp">Bergen-Belsenu</placeName>, <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP013_02.jpg" n="2"/> kde jsme byly
                    až do <term ref="#t573" type="subject">osvobození</term>.</p>
                <p>Podpis:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_schickova_helena" type="ehri">Schicková</persName>
                </p>
                <p>Protokol opsala:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_schickova_helena" type="ehri">Helena Schicková</persName>
                </p>
                <p>opsáno podle původního protokolu</p>
                <p>Popis svědků:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ehri_et_gerzonova_berta" type="ehri">B. Gerzonová</persName>
                </p>
                <p>Za <term ref="#t657" type="subject">dokumentační akci</term> přijal: <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev" type="ehri"
                        >Scheck</persName></p>
                <p>Za archiv:</p>
            </div>
            <div type="transcription">
                <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP013_01.jpg" n="1"/>
                <p rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Statement</p>
                <p>Copied from the original statement signed by Mrs. <persName ref="#ehri_et_morgensternova_ruth" type="ehri">Ruth
                        Morgensternová</persName>, residing in <placeName ref="#brno" type="ehri">Brno</placeName>, <placeName ref="#brno" type="ehri"
                        >Na ponávce</placeName> 10</p>
                <p>former <term ref="#t483" type="subject">prisoner</term> in the <placeName ref="#l42" type="camp">Bergen-Belsen</placeName><term
                        ref="#t496" type="subject">concentr. camp</term> and a <term ref="#t508" type="subject">labor camp</term> in <placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Estonia</placeName></p>
                <p><term ref="#t267" type="subject">Transport Be Theresienstadt</term> - <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri"
                        >Estonia</placeName>.</p>
                <p><date when="1942-09-01">I. IX. 1942</date>
                    <term ref="#t267" type="subject">departure from Theresienstadt</term>, direction <placeName ref="#l1032" type="ehri"
                        >Riga</placeName>. The journey went well; the escort was decent. The <term ref="#t522" type="subject">train</term> stands
                        in <placeName ref="#l1032" type="ehri">Riga</placeName> for a day and then rides on to <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia"
                        type="ehri">Estonia</placeName>. After a five-day journey, the <term ref="#t522" type="subject">train</term> stops 25 km from
                        <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinn</placeName> in <placeName ref="#raasiku" type="ehri">Raasiku</placeName>. The
                        <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term> and <orgName ref="#g356" type="ehri">SD</orgName>, with beautiful, blue buses, are
                    waiting for us there. We stand in front of the <term ref="#t522" type="subject">train</term> and one <term ref="#t1216"
                        type="subject">SSman</term> selects the young people who will apparently be walking. The rest are told to put away their
                    luggage and step onto the bus. We’ve heard no news of them since. We, the young ones (75 <term ref="#t825" type="subject"
                        >women</term> and about 150 <term ref="#t826" type="subject">men</term>), leave on trucks with all of the luggage from the
                        <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term> to the nearby <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">JAGALLA</placeName>
                    <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term>. It’s a <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term> in the middle of a forest, with
                    old, broken down <term ref="#t837" type="subject">buildings</term>, surrounded by a barbed wire fence. The <term ref="#t482"
                        type="subject">Lagerführer</term> is an <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Estonian</placeName>
                    <orgName ref="#g356" type="ehri">SDman</orgName>; his adjutant a Baltic <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject"
                        >German</term>. The guards are <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Estonian</placeName>. Our valuables and extra
                        <term ref="#t836" type="subject">clothes</term> are taken away on the first evening (body search). The next day, our <term
                        ref="#t836" type="subject">clothes</term> are returned. Three days later, they lead us to large <term ref="#t837"
                        type="subject">buildings</term> where we unpack and sort the items from our <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term>.
                    The <term ref="#t826" type="subject">men</term>, whom we glimpse from far away, are sent to <term ref="#t508" type="subject"
                        >work</term> in the forest. Only the <term ref="#t292" type="subject">sick</term> return to us, and they are sent away,
                    allegedly to <placeName ref="#tartu" type="ehri">Dorpat</placeName>, where there is an <term ref="#t282" type="subject"
                        >infirmary</term>. Supposedly, the rest of the <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term> is there, but we never heard
                    from any inhabitant of <placeName ref="#tartu" type="ehri">Dorpat</placeName> that there were Jews there. <term ref="#t825"
                        type="subject">Women</term> are treated well; <term ref="#t826" type="subject">men</term> fare far worse, especially when they
                        <term ref="#t508" type="subject">work</term> outside, where the <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri"
                        >Estonians</placeName> rob then and don’t give them anything to <term ref="#t832" type="subject">eat</term>. The <term
                        ref="#t832" type="subject">food</term> is not bad; connection to the outside world is impossible. In <date when="1942-10"
                        >October</date>, another <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term> arrives from <placeName
                        ref="#federal-republic-of-germany" type="ehri">Germany</placeName> (<placeName ref="#frankfurt-am-main" type="ehri"
                        >Frankfurt</placeName> and <placeName ref="#berlin" type="ehri">Berlin</placeName>). Once again, luggage and some of the
                    people go to <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Jagälla</placeName>. In <date when="1942-12">December</date>, a large <term
                        ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term> of <term ref="#t825" type="subject">women</term> leaves for <placeName
                        ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Revala (Tallinn)</placeName> and supposedly to <placeName ref="#tartu" type="ehri"
                        >Dorpat</placeName> (only the <term ref="#t274" type="subject">older</term> and <term ref="#t292" type="subject">sick</term>).
                    The rest of the <term ref="#t825" type="subject">women</term> (there are 45 of them and almost all are <term ref="#t279"
                        type="subject">Czech</term>) move into very nice <term ref="#t837" type="subject">buildings</term>. After their <term
                        ref="#t556" type="subject">work</term> in <term ref="#t48312" type="subject">Schleuse</term> is done, the <term ref="#t825"
                        type="subject">women</term> go to the forest to <term ref="#t556" type="subject">chop</term> down trees and <term ref="#t556"
                        type="subject">tear down</term> old buildings. The <term ref="#t556" type="subject">work</term> is very hard. In <date
                        when="1943-08">August 1943</date>, the rest of the <term ref="#t825" type="subject">women</term> leave for <placeName
                        ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinn</placeName>; the <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term> is liquidated. Before we
                    leave, most of our things are taken away from us. In <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinn</placeName>, we <term
                        ref="#t837" type="subject">live</term> in the central <term ref="#t669" type="subject">prison</term>, where we meet up with
                    the first <term ref="#t521" type="subject">transport</term>, and <term ref="#t556" type="subject">work</term> together doing
                    cleaning <term ref="#t556" type="subject">work</term> in the port under the supervision of the <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri"
                        >OT</orgName>. Here, we see the <term ref="#t826" type="subject">men</term> from our <term ref="#t521" type="subject"
                        >transport</term> who also return to the <term ref="#t669" type="subject">prison</term> after their <term ref="#t556"
                        type="subject">work</term> is done. The <term ref="#t832" type="subject">food</term> in <term ref="#t669" type="subject"
                        >prison</term> is terrible, but we can sometimes procure something for ourselves.</p>
                <p>In <date when="1943-12">December 1943</date>, all of the <term ref="#t825" type="subject">women</term> leave <placeName
                        ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinn</placeName> and go to <placeName ref="#ereda" type="ehri">EREDA</placeName> (about 30 km
                    from <placeName ref="#narva" type="ehri">Narva</placeName>). The <term ref="#t826" type="subject">men</term> remain in <placeName
                        ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinn</placeName>, and this is where we last hear from them in <date when="1944-03">March
                        1944</date>. <placeName ref="#ereda" type="ehri">Ereda</placeName> is a small <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term>. It
                    already houses about 1,000 Jews from <placeName ref="#republic-of-lithuania" type="ehri">Lithuania</placeName> (<placeName
                        ref="#vilnius" type="ehri">Vilnius</placeName> and <placeName ref="#kaunas" type="ehri">Kovno</placeName>) and <placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-latvia" type="ehri">Latvia</placeName>. They are <term ref="#t213" type="subject">lice-infested</term> and
                    without their belongings. In the surrounding area, there are several other similar <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camps</term>.
                    There are also several <term ref="#t279" type="subject">Czechs</term> there, arriving from <placeName ref="#l1032" type="ehri"
                        >Riga</placeName>. The <term ref="#t1216" type="subject">SS</term> has already taken leadership of it; guards are <placeName
                        ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Est.</placeName> and <orgName ref="#g433" type="ehri">O.T.</orgName> The <term
                        ref="#t832" type="subject">food</term> is bad, but we have the option to obtain things for ourselves, but only the fearless
                    among us attempt this. We <term ref="#t556" type="subject">work</term> in the forest and on the construction of a new <term
                        ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term> a few km away. There is <term ref="#t493" type="subject">typhus</term>; there are <term
                        ref="#t292" type="subject">sick people</term>; <term ref="#t274" type="subject">the elderly</term> and <term ref="#t824"
                        type="subject">children</term> are constantly sent away (most likely to <placeName ref="#l0" type="camp"
                    >Auschwitz</placeName>). When the <orgName ref="#g004583" type="ehri">Russians</orgName> approach (in <date when="1944-07">July
                        1944</date>), we depart for <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinn</placeName>, where a boat is supposed to be waiting
                    for us. It’s not there, and so we go to a suburb of <placeName ref="#tallinn" type="ehri">Tallinn</placeName> to a large meadow,
                    where we stay for three weeks with no <term ref="#t837" type="subject">shelter</term>. We <term ref="#t556" type="subject">dig
                        trenches</term>. There is <term ref="#t569" type="subject">famine</term> in the <term ref="#t508" type="subject">camp</term>.
                    In <date when="1944-08">August</date>, we finally sail to <placeName ref="#federal-republic-of-germany" type="ehri"
                        >Germany</placeName>. We sail for five days without <term ref="#t832" type="subject">food</term>. We arrive in <placeName
                        ref="#gdansk" type="ehri">Danzig</placeName> and sail down the <placeName ref="#ehri_et_vistula" type="ehri"
                        >Vistula</placeName> to <placeName ref="#l857" type="ehri">Stutthof</placeName>. There, we are sent to the baths, our
                    belongings are taken away, and we are given new <term ref="#t836" type="subject">clothes</term>. Our hair was already cut before
                    we left <placeName ref="#republic-of-estonia" type="ehri">Estonia</placeName>. <term ref="#t825" type="subject">Women</term> who
                    are capable of <term ref="#t556" type="subject">working</term> leave for <placeName ref="#hamburg" type="ehri">Hamburg</placeName>
                    after three weeks to <term ref="#t556" type="subject">work</term> in a munitions <term ref="#t929" type="subject">plant</term>.
                    From there, we are evacuated in <date when="1945-04">April 1945</date> to <placeName ref="#l42" type="camp"
                        >Bergen-Belsen</placeName>, <pb facs="EHRI-ET-JMP013_02.jpg" n="2"/> where we remain until <term ref="#t573" type="subject"
                        >liberation</term>.</p>
